<font color="#FF0000">THE WALL</font><br>
<tt>Thu Nov 28 10:54:05 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
THE WALL:  I've reflected on the words of so many complete strangers,how THE WALL affected them.  The names, frozen epitaphs in granite, etched by a history that only a few can embrace today.  I recall all those shining, youthful faces standing around me at the induction center.....listening to their distant chatter about baseball games, girl friends, wild parties, family and friends.  Not one, as I recall, ever fathomed the concept that somewhere stood other young men, gathered and indoctrinated by their &quot;elders&quot;, who, by the virtue of fate, spoke about their lives, their families and friends....but, all too soon would these unprepossessing young men be shattered by an experience that only conjecture and time could hope to allay.
<p><code>-- lgeorge@brandywine.net  (Lewis H. George, Jr.) </code><p>


